==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English ''heyewei'' < Old English ''[[heahweg|hēahweġ]]'' ("main road"), made from Old English ''[[heah|hēah]]'' (‘of great height,’ ‘lofty,’ ‘tall’) < Proto-Germanic ''*kaukhaz'' < Proto-Indo-European ''*koukos'' (‘hill’), + Old English [[weg#Old English|weg]] (‘road,’ ‘path’) < Proto-Germanic ''*wegaz'' < Proto-Indo-European base ''*wegh-'' (‘to move’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈhaɪweɪ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A main, direct, [[public]] [[road]].
# A multi-lane, high speed thoroughfare connecting major population centers.

